Next, we choose a pivot element from the array. This pivot element will be used to partition the array into two subarrays. We can choose any element from the array as the pivot, but it is common to choose the last element in the array because it ensures that the pivot is not too small compared to the other elements.

Once we have chosen the pivot element, we partition the array into two subarrays. We do this by iterating through the array and moving all elements that are less than or equal to the pivot to the left subarray, and all elements that are greater than the pivot to the right subarray.

After partitioning the array, we recursively sort the left and right subarrays using the quicksort algorithm. This ensures that the subarrays are also sorted.

Finally, we return the sorted array.

